job_description:
Job Objective
• * Lead OS/BSP software design for Digital Cockpit, ADAS Domain Controller and Telematics products, including requirements analysis, preliminary design, detailed design/review, technical documentation and E2E delivery for specific project
• Design and implement platform architecture based on SOC Virtualization Linux/QNX/RTOS/Android to meet various products requirements
• Responsible for OS/BSP software requirements discussion and clarification, technical solution review with main partners, like RFI/RFQ, etc.
• Responsible for software platform infrastructure build-up, improvement, and iterative optimization
• Lead the software technical evaluation of main chip, including SOC, MCU and main peripherals
• Responsible for platform software performance KPI definition and platform software scalability design
• Responsible for board Bring-up, including SOC/MCU, OS porting, Bootloader, Drivers and debug
• System Performance & Stability tuning, such as Computational force optimization, I/O resource, CPU & Memory usage, etc.
• Scouting advanced technologies and landing them to platform software

Qualification

Education

B.S. or higher degree in Electrical/Electronic or Computer Science Engineering;

Experience

At least 6 years working experience in platform software, such as BSP, OS, middleware for various vehicle products

Knowledge

Thorough knowledge and understanding of ARM and SOC architecture and develop tools-chain;

Thorough knowledge and understanding MCU and CP/AP AutoSAR;

Good experience and sense on platform software design, such as high scalability and reliability, low coupling;

Experience in leading platform design for cockpit (or ADAS controller) with whole lifecycle;

Proficient at Linux/QNX/Android/RTOS, kernel, IPC/IDC, performance tuning;

Good knowledge of Multi-Media Framework, Display/Audio/Camera/Ethernet/ driver, GPIO, SPI, etc.;

Proficient at C/C /assembly language programming skill is a must;

Familiar with SOA concept and implement guidance;

Enthusiastic to In-vehicle infotainment and smart cockpit related products and solutions;

Strong communication and interpersonal skills;

Good oral and written English;
